  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (fd90b1d 2023-11-06T20:45:35.983698000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nHi, I noticed that `blockhash` returns the block number, not a random value now.\r\nIn my project, a test that assumes `blockhash` is somewhat random was not passed, so I found this.\r\nMaybe the spec was changed to that, I think `blockhash` should be random.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport {Test, console2} from \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract CounterTest is Test {\r\n\r\n    function testBlockNumber() public {\r\n        vm.roll(10);\r\n        console2.log(uint256(blockhash(block.number - 1)));\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ forge test -vvvvv\r\n[⠰] Compiling...\r\n[⠢] Compiling 1 files with 0.8.22\r\n[⠆] Solc 0.8.22 finished in 1.71s\r\nCompiler run successful!\r\n\r\nRunning 1 test for test/Counter.t.sol:CounterTest\r\n[PASS] testBlockNumber() (gas: 6036)\r\nLogs:\r\n  9\r\n\r\nTraces:\r\n  [6036] CounterTest::testBlockNumber() \r\n    ├─ [0] VM::roll(10) \r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    ├─ [0] console::log(9) [staticcall]\r\n    │   └─ ← ()\r\n    └─ ← ()\r\n\r\nTest result: ok. 1 passed; 0 failed; 0 skipped; finished in 1.08ms\r\n \r\nRan 1 test suites: 1 tests passed, 0 failed, 0 skipped (1 total tests)\r\n```",
